// ⛔ DO NOT DEPLOY THIS FILE. It is intentionally NOT the live ruleset.
//
// The Firestore rules for transport-freight live in the SHARED "unico-operations"
// project, alongside every other UNICO app. This repo used to carry a stale copy
// whose transportfreight block was wide open:
//     match /apps/transportfreight/{collection}/{docId}
//       { allow read, write: if request.auth != null; }
// Pasting that into the live console would REOPEN transport-freight data to any
// signed-in (including anonymous) device and undo the role-based lockdown.
//
// ✅ Canonical, deployable rules:  ~/attendance-app/firestore.rules
// ✅ Deploy them with:             node ~/attendance-app/jobs/deployRules.js
//    (pulls live first + backs up to attendance-app/jobs/rules_backup/)
//
// The transportfreight block there is role-based (tfIsOwner / tfIsManager /
// tfIsGaadiwala) — gaadiwala reads only his own transporterId, no hard-deletes,
// settlements immutable, masters/users are nonAnon-read. Keep that as the source
// of truth; never resurrect an "if request.auth != null" copy here.
